    <briefdescription>
<para>Type-erased wrapper for game world managers. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1Manager" kindref="compound">Manager</ref> uses the Concept/Model pattern to erase the concrete manager type. Concrete managers are plain classes that satisfy `IsManagerLike&lt;T&gt;` (i.e. provide `flush(<ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1UpdateContext" kindref="compound">UpdateContext</ref>&amp;)` and declare `using EngineRoleTag = ManagerRole;`).</para>
<para>The internal `Concept` base defines the virtual interface, and `Model&lt;T&gt;` adapts the concrete type T, owning it by value. `init()` and `reset()` are conditionally forwarded if the concrete type satisfies `HasInit&lt;T&gt;` or `HasReset&lt;T&gt;` respectively.</para>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1Manager" kindref="compound">Manager</ref> is move-only (non-copyable).</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para>IsManagerLike </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>ManagerRole </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="namespacehelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1a12c55c47caeb5dc7588c1b1e74f4992f" kindref="member">ManagerRegistry</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>ConceptModelRegistry </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
